{{de/Community/Junctionary/Kreuzungsmenü}}

Ähnlich der [[de/Community/Junctionary/Halb Umgemodelt|halb umgemodelten]] Kreuzung, aber mit Tunnel anstatt von Brücken und manche Gleise kommen an anderen Stellen zusammen.

[[File:en/Community/Junctionary/Ultimate 3way junction.png|frame|none|Ultimative 3-Weg Kreuzung]]

{{en/Community/Junctionary/Junction Criteria|Mittel|2|1|0|3|1|1|1|1|0|0|0||Ausgefallene Züge beeinflussen eine Strecke.|

'''Pro'''
*Hohe Geschwindigkeit.
*Hohe Verkehrskapazität.
*Stau ist unwahrscheinlich.
*Kleine Fläche
*Keine scharfen Kurven, kann mühelos für jede Zuglänge gebaut werden.
*Angemessener Warteplatz für abbiegende Züge.

'''Cons'''
*Signaling gaps from tunnels. (doubling tunnels makes junction at least 2x2 tiles larger and harder to build)

'''Tips'''
*Start by building the "short diagonal" track first. Make its length equal to your longest train.
}}


==Variations==
Here's a slightly different mainline example:

[[File:en/Community/Junctionary/3way-over-under.jpeg|none|thumb|600px|3-way over-under]]

{{en/Community/Junctionary/Junction Criteria|Average|3|1|1|4|0|1|1|1|0|0|0||Broken down trains affect one line.|

'''Pros'''
*High traffic capacity.

'''Cons'''
*Slow, unless tracks are diagonal.
*Jams more likely than in ultimate 3-way junction.
*Requires space between tracks.
*Sharp turns, unless tracks are diagonal.
*Not enough waiting space for turning trains.
*Signaling gaps from bridges and tunnels.
*Bridges slow down high-speed maglev trains.
}}

